  "prompt": "Is there an app that gives you recipes based on what you have in the fridge?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several apps designed to help you find recipes based on the ingredients you already have at home. Here are a few popular ones:\n\n1. **Supercook**: This app allows you to input the ingredients you have, and it will generate a list of recipes you can make with those items. It also provides step-by-step instructions for cooking.\n\n2. **Allrecipes Dinner Spinner**: While primarily a recipe app, Allrecipes also has a feature where you can search for recipes based on specific ingredients.\n\n3. **Yummly**: Yummly offers personalized recipe recommendations and allows you to filter recipes based on the ingredients you have. It also considers dietary preferences and restrictions.\n\n4. **BigOven**: BigOven has a \"Use Up Leftovers\" feature where you can input up to three ingredients, and it will suggest recipes that include those items.\n\n5. **RecipeKeeper**: This app helps you organize your recipes and also has a feature to search for recipes based on the ingredients you have.\n\n6. **Cookpad**: Cookpad allows users to upload recipes and search for recipes based on the ingredients they have.\n\n7. **SideChef**: This app provides guided recipes and allows you to search for recipes based on the ingredients you have. It also includes voice commands for hands-free cooking.\n\nThese apps can be very useful for reducing food waste and making the most of what you already have in your kitchen.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
